<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,438,645]" box="[151,639,474,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,248,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,198,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-32@66.[201,1387,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 13. Southeast Asian Eudocima and Eudocima sikhimensis group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605531/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 13</figureCitation>
: C–D, 20: I, 26: C–D, 32: A, 95: J)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,438,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
The forewings are reddish brown with green flecks like 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[768,941,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mionopastea">
<emphasis box="[768,941,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. mionopastea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the inner margin is more deeply concave proximal to the tornal hook. The hindwing marginal band is closer to the outer margin and is more dentate at the veins than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[300,460,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikhimensis">
<emphasis box="[300,460,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. sikhimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The forewing has a conspicuous greenish patch above the inner margin at the base and proximal to the PM line that is absent in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[608,737,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrannus">
<emphasis box="[608,737,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. tyrannus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Banziger &amp; Honey" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[791,918,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantia">
<emphasis box="[791,918,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. aurantia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1197,619,645]" name="Indonesia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
